Insights

🔹 1. Peak-Based Insights 
• Maharashtra recorded the highest confirmed case peaks, especially around April.
• These peaks were continuous during April–May, after which peaks became more distributed across states.
• In June, Bihar recorded the highest deaths.
• Kerala showed the highest recoveries in May.

🔹 2. State Dominance 
• Maharashtra has the highest confirmed, recovered, and deceased counts overall.
• This dominance is influenced by population size and scale.
• Kerala is the second major contributor, especially in confirmed and recovered cases.

🔹 3. Proportion-Based Insight (Very Important)
• Although total confirmed cases are high, total recoveries are also high.
• Deaths are comparatively low relative to confirmed cases.
• Recovery-to-confirmed ratio is high → positive sign.
• Death-to-confirmed ratio is low → controlled mortality.

🔹 6. Recovery Rate Trend 
• Initial months → high recovery rate
• Followed by a dip (reduced recovery efficiency)
• Low phase continues until April
• May–June → sharp increase and peak
• After June → decrease and stabilization

🔹 7. Death Rate Trend
• Initially decreasing trend
• Increase begins around May
• Peak observed in June
• After June → decline and stable behavior till December.


