State-Wise Covid Performance Analysis.

🔹 Rajasthan

Rajasthan demonstrated strong early performance with consistently high recovery rates, while maintaining a low death rate, indicating effective early-stage management.

🔹 Odisha

Odisha maintained one of the lowest death rates with minimal fluctuations, reflecting a stable and controlled healthcare response.

🔹 Maharashtra

Maharashtra experienced significant peaks in recovery and deaths, especially around June, indicating high activity levels driven by large case volumes rather than consistent performance.

🔹 Madhya Pradesh

Madhya Pradesh showed consistently low recovery rates along with a mid-period increase in death rate, indicating a relatively weaker recovery system under stress.

🔹 Kerala

Kerala maintained consistently low recovery rates but achieved one of the lowest death rates, suggesting a controlled system prioritizing patient survival.

🔹 Jharkhand

Jharkhand showed continuous presence in later months with both high and low recovery appearances, indicating unstable and fluctuating performance.

🔹 Bihar

Bihar exhibited mixed behavior with both high and low recovery rates, along with a mid-period death spike, reflecting inconsistent system performance.

🔹 Andhra Pradesh

Andhra Pradesh showed improvement over time, with recovery rates increasing after an unstable early phase, while maintaining a low death rate.

🔹 Assam

Assam displayed continuous mid-period activity with fluctuating recovery rates, indicating an unstable but active system over time.
